nodes.title: Automation
widgets_values:
Lap Counter: It increases the skip frames after every queue automatically according to the batch range set by you. 

1) Enter Batch Range (10 is good) 
2) After the first run it will tell the number n of queues you need in the Laps Needed Node.

3) Change The Control_After_Generate to "Increment" when ready for automation

4) Press the Queue Prompt Button n times till your Queue Size = N in the side menu. Or use Extra's Batch Option.  

It will automatically stop if you by mistakenly entered more laps, with no images found error, which is fine, no need to worry.

nodes.title: #2_7 Animate Anyone Raw
widgets_values:
HOW TO USE: 

*Download and load all the Animate Anyone models in proper folder (See Load Models Note)  

1) Upload a full body reference Image in the load image node [Purple Node]. 
2) Enter the Output path for saving the raw images [Blue Node].
3) Enter Openpose Directory in the [Neon Pink Node] (It should be already exported by #1 Passes Extractor file) 
4) Enter Batch Range (Minimum 10) 

Background distorts according to the Range, longer range has more wobble. Use higer range (<10) only when you have a more than 8 GB else frequent out of memory issue. 

5) Play Lap Counter for automation [Red Node]. (See note for more details) 

6) Hit Queue. 






-----------------------------------------

nodes.title: Image Loading and Resizing
widgets_values:
1) Since Animate Anyone is trained on 512x768 resolution, Input Reference Images close to this dimension. 

2) Load Portrait full body images which are facing in the front with face, hands, legs fully visible and no overlapping. This will give best output.  

3) Resize: OpenPose Images will be of Different dimension, Put Resize values in ratio to the open pose image dimension.  Do not worry if there is little stretching or squashing of the image, it will be fixed in the refiner file. 

4) Keep Background simple or plain (which does not have objects), because it going to wobble a lot in the background.

Tip: For every batch change, it will be inconsistent, use value to around 10-12 in the "start refiner from nth step" to reduce this inconsistency. inside the refiner file.
